Added a numHintsSeen/numHints counter display inside the Hint button in the client. Moved the location of the topic/standard div to 650 down from the content div so no overlap happens on tall problems that are taking up 600 px
fixed bug in tutorhut.js so that it shows (0) instead of (0/0) when a problem has no hints

Change isTest handling so that isTest=false and no p1-p5 parameters will result in showing a tutor that has no test controls and not show problems marked testable. This meant creating having to temp user types: externalTempCaller and externalTempTester. The caller gets no test controls and only sees ready content. The tester gets controls and sees testable content in addition to ready content. Neither updates stats. This allows testing the system and seeing it as a real user would see it. I've left the default to be isTest=true if this param is not provided.
Discovered a bug that is handled by reporting an exception. If a non test user tries to teachTopic and that topic has no ready problems (all are testable) then we can't show anything. The best we can do is return an exception reporting that you need to call the system with isTest=true if there arent any ready problems in a topic

Release 1/21/15.
Bug fix for TeachTopic events with lessonIds pointing to content with problems in integrity. Added some error checks. Made it load the lessons at servlet init time just to check it and generate messages.
Fixed bug with logback URL for assistments. We went back to a fixed URL rather than trying to get it from the referer header which wasn't present on calls from Assistments.

Fixed bug for TeachTopic&problemId=XXX where XXX is a quickAuth problem. We were not sending the form=quickAuth to the client so that it correctly use the skeleton . Added in a form variable to instantiate globals.form in the mathspring.jsp

Added logging so I can see what happens when instantiating pedagogical models . Bug fix: Assistments requires partnerSpecificData be included in JSON so I put it back in and tested with debugger and got back 201 status and from POSTMAN REST. This JSON is GOOD!

fixed hint selection so do not return hints that are marked with givesAnswer=1. Also modified the number of hints that are calculated for numHints sent to client (doesn't count hints that give answer)
